<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11480] ClientScanner might not close the HConnection created in construction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11480</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ClientScanner will create HConnection in its construction:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; ClientScanner(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Configuration conf, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Scan scan,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] tableName) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;(conf, scan, tableName, HConnectionManager.getConnection(conf));
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, this connection won&apos;t be closed in ClientScanner.close(). Is it better to deprecate this construction?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
